==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Colugo
<hw>Co*lu"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. an
aboriginal name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A peculiar East Indian
mammal (<spn>Galleopithecus volans</spn>), having along the sides,
connecting the fore and hind limbs, a parachutelike membrane, by means
of which it is able to make long leaps, like the flying squirrel; --
called also <altname>flying lemur</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Columba</ent>⟦br⟧
